          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Inflammatory_bowel_disease"
        },
        {
          "text": "Rheumatoid arthritis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Rheumatoid_arthritis"
        },
        {
          "text": "Granulomatosis with polyangiitis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Granulomatosis_with_polyangiitis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Essential sign is scleral edema, usually accompanied by violaceous discoloration of the globe\nIntense\nocular pain\nthat radiates to the face\nPain with EOM (extraocular muscles insert into the sclera)\nPhotophobia\nGlobe tenderness to palpation\nEpiscleral vessel dilation",
      "subsections": {
        "Posterior_Scleritis": {
          "text": "Posterior to the insertion of the extraocular muscles\nPhysical exam often benign\nInflammation may sometimes be seen at the extremes of gaze\nPatient complains of pain, pain upon EOM\nInvolvement of the optic nerve and retina is common\nRetinal detachment\n, optic disc edema",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Complications": {
          "text": "Cornea (peripheral ulcerative keratitis → irreversible\nloss of vision\n)\nUveal tract (anterior\nuveitis\nseen in 40% - spillover of inflammation from the sclera)\nPosterior segment (\nretinal detachment\n, optic disc edema)",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
